patefact is a DEFENSIVE security-measurement and research tool. It exists
to measure and classify the prevalence of misconfigured, publicly exposed
open directories, and to do so with harm-avoidance engineered into its
architecture (off-host capture, no PII/CSAM capture, hash-and-discard,
passive lookup-only enrichment, aggregate reporting).

